e control given the characteristics of the requesting browser. Browser definition files are used by the <xref:System.Web.HttpBrowserCapabilities> class to identify the characteristics of the client browser and map the adapter to the browser type. For more information, see [Architectural Overview of Adaptive Control Behavior](../Topic/Architectural%20Overview%20of%20Adaptive%20Control%20Behavior.md).  \\n  \\n For a description of the adaptive rendering architecture of ASP.NET and a step-by-step walkthrough that shows how to implement a control adapter and map it to a control, see \\\"Authoring ASP.NET Server Control Adapters: An Introduction\\\" in the MSDN Library at [http://msdn.microsoft.com/library](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library).\"\n  example:\n  - \"The following code example shows how to extend the HideDisabledControlAdapter class to display a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Label> control in an enabled and disabled state. This example contains three parts:  \\n  \\n-   An adapter derived from the HideDisabledControlAdapter class.  \\n  \\n-   The .aspx file that incorporates the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Label> control and device-specific content.  \\n  \\n-   A browser file to link the adapter to a device type.  \\n  \\n The following code example demonstrates how to extend the HideDisabledControlAdapter class.  \\n  \\n [!code-cs[System.Web.UI.WebControls.Adapters.HideDisabledControlAdapter#1](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_209_1.cs)]\\n [!code-vb[System.Web.UI.WebControls.Adapters.HideDisabledControlAdapter#1](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_209_1.vb)]  \\n  \\n The following code example demonstrates how to declare a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Label> control with device-specific content.  \\n  \\n [!code-cs[System.Web.UI.WebControls.Adapters.HideDisabledControlAdapter#3](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_209_2.aspx)]\\n [!code-vb[System.Web.UI.WebControls.Adapters.HideDisabledControlAdapter#3](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_209_2.aspx)]  \\n  \\n The following code example shows how to link the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Label> control to the custom adapter for browsers running on Windows CE .NET.  \\n  \\n [!code-cs[XpsCreate#XpsCreateAddPkgContent](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/XpsCreate/XpsCreate.cs#xpscreateaddpkgcontent)]\"\n  syntax:\n    content: 'public class HideDisabledControlAdapter : System.Web.UI.WebControls.Adapters.WebControlAdapter'\n  inheritance:\n  - System.Object\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter\n  - System.Web.UI.WebControls.Adapters.WebControlAdapter\n  implements: []\n  inheritedMembers:\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.BeginRender(System.Web.UI.HtmlTextWriter)\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.Browser\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.CreateChildControls\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.EndRender(System.Web.UI.HtmlTextWriter)\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.LoadAdapterControlState(System.Object)\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.LoadAdapterViewState(System.Object)\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.OnInit(System.EventArgs)\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.OnLoad(System.EventArgs)\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.OnPreRender(System.EventArgs)\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.OnUnload(System.EventArgs)\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.Page\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.PageAdapter\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.RenderChildren(System.Web.UI.HtmlTextWriter)\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.SaveAdapterControlState\n  - System.Web.UI.Adapters.ControlAdapter.SaveAdapterViewState\n  - System.Web.UI.WebControls.Adapters.WebControlAdapter.Control\n  - System.Web.UI.WebControls.Adapters.WebControlAdapter.IsEnabled\n  - System.Web.UI.WebControls.Adapters.WebControlAdapter.RenderBeginTag(System.Web.UI.HtmlTextWriter)\n  - System.Web.UI.WebControls.Adapters.WebC